eastside college prep tltl visit transformative learning technologies laboratory home about publications projects people teaching media fablearn 2011 home tltl in the news eastside college prep tltl visit eastside college prep tltl visit image eastside college prep was founded in 1996 by stanford graduates chris bischof and helen kim eastside college prep was founded in 1996 by stanford graduates chris bischof and helen kim ecp filled a void that had been left 20 years before when east palo alto's only high school closed today eastside has grown to 280 students in grades 6 through 12 18 eastside high schoolers visited the tlt lab in early july for an intense 8 day workshop after meeting the staff and getting acquainted with the machines around the lab they embarked on their own projects the prompt was to design a prototype for a product or device that would improve one's everyday life working in groups of three the students were encouraged to think outside the box collaborate closely with their teammates and utilize the lab's resources to the fullest extent after a fruitful brainstorming session the six teams were off to a running start the students made accounts on the stanford maker's club website and posted about their experience in the lab after every session each team wrote about their difficulties and triumphs in designing and building their projects and got a chance to see what the other teams were up to the final projects ranged from a miniature car that preemptively stops in front of obstacles to a trashcan that beeps when it is full to a very innovative cat toy eastside college preparatory school homepage transformative learning technologies lab school of education stanford university 520 galvez mall room 102 ceras building stanford california 94305 usa connect with us connect with us on facebook connect with us on twitter connect with us on youtube connect with us on flickr copyright 2011 all rights reserved top
